Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.31,0:01:48.28,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,460)}Ep. 42 - A Child Called Emily
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.60,0:01:58.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We concluded that Lucy\Nmight have gone to see Dr. Deighton.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.39,0:02:03.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and I went to the city of Gawler to look for Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.30,0:02:05.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she wasn't there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.66,0:02:08.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just where might Lucy be now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.81,0:02:11.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It could be that she returned home by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.43,0:02:12.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I hope for.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.39,0:02:14.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.55,0:02:15.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.51,0:02:18.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You also think Lucy didn't really return?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.51,0:02:20.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.30,0:02:23.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy cannot spend more than one night\Nrunning away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:25.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'll return.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.30,0:02:26.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:28.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, we need to get home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:38.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! No! You'll fall out if you twitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.50,0:02:40.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, Little. Everything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.78,0:02:43.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The carriage can only go a little faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:46.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, there's a carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.45,0:03:02.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Silver, you're too noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:07.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, and it's Mr. Pettywell's carriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:10.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:14.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Popple!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.70,0:03:16.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:18.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Been to the Gawler, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:19.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.19,0:03:24.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That means you also went there\Nto look at Princeton's farm, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:25.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.61,0:03:30.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No need to deny it. Princeton's farm\Nis one spectacular farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:33.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is this Princeton's farm you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.32,0:03:35.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be feigning ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:39.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad for you, though.\NI'm going to buy that farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:42.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's the best farm in all of Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.21,0:03:44.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, make haste, Ferguson!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.83,0:03:50.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:52.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think Mr. Pettywell got some wrong idea about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.81,0:03:57.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It seems, he thinks we went there\Nto look at a certain farm for sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.81,0:03:59.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The Princeton's farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.60,0:04:01.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Princeton's farm, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:06.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, I'm in no position\Nto be buying any farm regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.19,0:04:16.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:18.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:28.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily! Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:36.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so you were here, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.05,0:04:40.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. You've been calling out to me for a while, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.25,0:04:44.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. You're still to grow accustomed\Nto being called Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.29,0:04:45.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:50.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Any other name would do too.\NDo you have a name you like the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:53.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in that case,\Nlet's settle on Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.90,0:04:54.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.57,0:04:57.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't there a parrot perching on your hand just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.58,0:05:05.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That bird must be very sociable\Nto be sitting on your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.82,0:05:07.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I called it and it came.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.30,0:05:09.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.55,0:05:12.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I managed to understand a little more about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:16.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You remembered something?\NAbout your home? About your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:19.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I realized something about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:21.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's that I love the animals very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.29,0:05:25.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. That's why the bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:31.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe what a good girl you are, Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You smell very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:39.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.09,0:05:43.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When you do this,\NI feel like it's my mother embracing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.91,0:05:44.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.91,0:05:45.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:47.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Try calling me mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.00,0:05:54.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that is, of course,\Nuntil you regain your own memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.69,0:05:56.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please, try to call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.99,0:05:59.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.89,0:06:04.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.29,0:06:05.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:07.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.69,0:06:11.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily. Emily...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.59,0:06:20.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, you have a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:22.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:24.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost dinner time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.10,0:06:28.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They said they absolutely need to see you by today...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:29.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:31.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.12,0:06:32.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that man, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:34.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.59,0:06:39.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I turn him down,\Nhe's not the kind of man who'd just meekly go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:42.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take him to the reading room, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:43.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:49.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:53.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, Emily called me mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.61,0:06:55.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, but she's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:07:00.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,While she stays here, I asked her to call me mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.16,0:07:02.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. But still, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:02.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You have a visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:03.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:10.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, dear, I still think it's a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:11.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.04,0:07:12.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:17.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Later... We'll talk it through later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:20.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.82,0:07:23.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me in your room upstairs, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:24.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.19,0:07:58.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:03.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening. We've not met\Nin a long while. Are you well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:05.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, I'm doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.12,0:08:06.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what is your business here?
Comment: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:08.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:12.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,May I sit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:13.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:17.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty impressive, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.83,0:08:18.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.62,0:08:23.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This library. I'm sure you're the most avid book collector in all of Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:25.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:30.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, would you tell me what is your business here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.65,0:08:36.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, I went to look at your farm today\Nand found it extremely to my liking, Mr. Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.10,0:08:37.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which farm do you refer to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:40.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I have farms scattered all across the region.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:43.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The one near the city of Gawler.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:46.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? That is one remarkable farm indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.80,0:08:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How does 500 pound sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.01,0:08:50.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:51.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.20,0:08:53.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.61,0:08:57.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, but I don't understand what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:01.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, 1,500 pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:02.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's stop it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.10,0:09:04.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When did I ever say that I'm selling that farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.63,0:09:06.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're not selling it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:10.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I definitely have no such intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:15.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's not true.\NI know Popple went to look at it before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.21,0:09:18.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right? You promised to sell it to Popple, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:20.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Popple?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.43,0:09:21.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.99,0:09:24.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't feign ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.24,0:09:27.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm absolutely serious.\NI don't know a man by the name of Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:33.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily? Emily. My name is Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:37.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And my mother's name is Sylvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.70,0:09:42.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not right.\NI... Who am I, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:53.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell me, who am I really, Prospero?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.14,0:09:54.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.09,0:09:59.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:05.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about it, and I can't help feeling\Nthat Lucy didn't really run away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.70,0:10:08.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why won't she return?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:11.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There must be something else,\Npreventing her from returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.56,0:10:12.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.91,0:10:14.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:19.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that although she wants to return,\Nthere must be something standing in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:21.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you suppose she's been kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:23.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kidnapped? No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:28.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I also don't think it's so,\Nbut what if someone {\i1}did{\i0} kidnap her for some reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:31.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, wouldn't it be better to seek help from police?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We should at least let them know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:37.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask the police to look for her,\NI'm sure they'll find her in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:51.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little miss!\NYour dinner is ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:52.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:05.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep in mind that I won't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:10.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. Let me put it in no uncertain terms for you:\NI am firmly unwilling to part with that farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:28.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? After me, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:31.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come one, hurry! We need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:38.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have something\Nagainst the stairs, Prospero? Come!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.71,0:11:39.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.11,0:11:41.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.56,0:11:46.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This way, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:48.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:12.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come, don't be shy now.\NYou can sit here, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.09,0:12:13.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.79,0:12:22.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you like that bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:24.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.80,0:12:28.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If there's something you don't like,\Njust tell Carol and she'll take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.14,0:12:32.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. But I really like everything the way it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:35.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.30,0:12:37.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.39,0:12:39.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could you call me that once again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:40.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.27,0:12:41.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Call me mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.40,0:12:45.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine even if you only whisper it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.81,0:12:49.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:55.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good heavens, what a nasty man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.80,0:13:14.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:21.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A nasty man, I'm telling you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:22.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your recent visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:26.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That man by the name of Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.75,0:13:28.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.02,0:13:32.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I like it very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.19,0:13:37.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a pleasant happening, Sylvia?\NEating dinner with a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:38.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:43.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, we can't just let her\Nstay in our house indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.92,0:13:45.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You do understand, don't you, Sylvia?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.17,0:14:05.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I feel like I'm full already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:08.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But you've barely eaten anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:12.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have no appetite either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:15.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is my cooking that bad today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.29,0:14:18.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that. It's as delicious as any other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.59,0:14:23.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is too worried about Lucy\Nto be in the mood for eating, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.13,0:14:25.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.82,0:14:28.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't Lucy return home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.00,0:14:31.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to know that too, Tob.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.61,0:14:36.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm about to say\Nwill probably only aggravate everyone's worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.20,0:14:39.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible that Lucy's absence is not due to her own volition,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:42.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but rather, she can't return due to an external factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:45.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She'll come back for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.96,0:14:48.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,O-Of course, I also think she will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:51.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She returned, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:54.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.77,0:14:56.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! She returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.70,0:15:00.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.89,0:15:03.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's a fortunate time I returned at.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.22,0:15:08.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.01,0:15:12.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I hope there's some left for me.\NI'm as hungry as a wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.98,0:15:15.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:17.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody even said "welcome back."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:19.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.81,0:15:22.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, I've finished already,\Nso you can sit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.73,0:15:24.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.70,0:15:30.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I won't get to go home this week,\Nbut as luck would have it, I got a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:33.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:36.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:42.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Everyone is kinda strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:43.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:47.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Lucy isn't here. Did she fall ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:16:02.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you have to read so many books?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:04.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm reading them because I like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.61,0:16:05.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The books?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.72,0:16:06.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.94,0:16:09.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I even went to all the trouble\Nof delivering them here from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:13.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,England?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:17.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't remember anything about England?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.42,0:16:18.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.10,0:16:20.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.92,0:16:23.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like it's the first time I'm seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:25.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's called a globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.21,0:16:26.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A globe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.22,0:16:27.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:28.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, please sit here for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.93,0:16:32.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, you must remember well\Nwhat I'm about to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.79,0:16:35.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, this here is Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.12,0:16:38.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's been four years since we, the white people,\Nhave come to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.99,0:16:42.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The people living here now, for the most part,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.40,0:16:46.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,came here on ships from England\Nand other various countries of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:50.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is England, this is Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.11,0:16:51.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is France.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:52.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,France?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.42,0:16:54.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Did that ring any bell for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:59.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you used to be French?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.29,0:17:00.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:06.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You had to endure a long ship voyage to get here.\NPlease try to think of and recall the sea and the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.99,0:17:16.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very curious condition indeed.\NThis, what the call amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:21.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Some tea for the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:27.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use. She can't remember a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:31.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, listen, you don't have to rush things so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:34.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing this with her parents' feelings in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.30,0:17:39.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It could be that Emily lost her memory a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:41.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And also that her parents abandoned her...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.30,0:17:42.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sylvia!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.20,0:17:49.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Emily, try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.34,0:17:52.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you still have some memories\Nfrom a long time ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:56.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.39,0:18:01.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She's such an adorable child.\NI'm sure her parents are searching for her far and wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:16.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:21.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to the police station now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:27.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to come with us, Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.72,0:18:41.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little is one truly intelligent fella.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.89,0:19:02.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Uh... I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:05.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.83,0:19:09.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want to report a missing child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:14.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to ask the police for help with the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:27.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I almost feel like a kind of queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.49,0:19:36.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm seriously worried now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.72,0:19:38.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it about that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.41,0:19:40.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.89,0:19:42.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:46.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is unsettling. Our own daughter Emily\Ndied when she was two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.89,0:19:50.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, you call that girl Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:51.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How is that a bad thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.93,0:19:54.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That girl isn't Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.13,0:19:56.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You could choose {\i1}any{\i0} other name!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.12,0:19:59.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only until she remembers her real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.19,0:20:01.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you make her call you mother, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:07.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm well aware of how much you're yearning to have a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:09.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that girl isn't Emily who is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.30,0:20:12.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she is oh-so adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:14.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true, she's adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:17.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she's still someone else's child, not ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.57,0:20:22.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, dear. If... If it so happens that Emily\Nnever recovers her memory.,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.26,0:20:26.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look... Look, you're already considering\N{\i1}that{\i0} kind of prospect!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.90,0:20:31.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. She {\i1}will{\i0} recover her memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:34.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you intend to become a real mother one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.60,0:20:37.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing yourself a heavy blow\Nby what you're doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.10,0:20:43.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't believe how much\NI'm worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:31.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.00,0:21:40.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:42.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:46.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily! Emily...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.68,0:21:55.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The police are short on staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.90,0:21:59.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so they can't afford arranging a search party\Nfor those who run away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.55,0:22:02.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But how do they know\Nshe'd not been abducted by a criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.39,0:22:06.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If that had been so,\Nwe'd have received a ransom demand already.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.69,0:22:10.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, in that case,\Nthe police would get on it at once, they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.36,0:22:13.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, we just have to keep looking for her on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.02,0:22:17.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With John's help,\Nwe'll start the search in earnest tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.50,0:22:19.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's the only thing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:22.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we'll take Little along.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.44,0:22:23.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good. We'll do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.74,0:23:04.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little? Little!
Comment: 0,0:23:16.99,0:23:18.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.00,0:23:21.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.00,0:23:23.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.94,0:23:47.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When we woke up in the morning,\NLittle was already gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:05.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Am I Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.28,0:24:11.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In order to find my family,\NUncle Frank put out a notice in the local newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.01,0:24:14.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Passed By".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.59,0:24:16.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
